> Is this PR valid for `Minus` ?
> I mean `sameRelCollectionNoOrderConsidered ` is not enough for validation checking.

@jinxing64 Thanks for review, you are right, `MinusOnCalcsToMinusUnifyRule` should not be implemented, it may cause data errors.

@hsyuan , have you seen this discussion?
https://github.com/apache/calcite/pull/784#discussion_r245797826

Can you provide an explanation and/or a test case to elaborate on why the current implementation is not right?

I add a test case in RelToSqlConverterTest, it seems to produce a correct sql
```
@Test public void testGroupByWithLimitPlan() {
    String query = "SELECT sum(\"salary\") FROM \"employee\" group by \"gender\" limit 10";
    sql(query)
        .ok("SELECT SUM(\"salary\")\n"
            + "FROM \"foodmart\".\"employee\"\n"
            + "GROUP BY \"gender\"\n"
            + "FETCH NEXT 10 ROWS ONLY");
  }
```

@danny0405 I tried to send an email to @julianhyde to remind the status of this PR, but Julian might just be busy recently. (I also tried to ask for help from other people in community but people generally is busy recently)

So if there is no response on this PR, could we just merge it next week? I can send an email to community as a reminder a few days before we do the merging. 

Util this moment I don't think there are major issues about the design of TUMBLE TVF, so SQL syntax of it will remain like what it is now. I will be willing to fix any following comment/issue in the future.

